#1 Download work statation/ virtual box
https://my.vmware.com/en/web/vmware/downloads/info/slug/desktop_end_user_computing/vmware_workstation_pro/15_0


#2 Install workstation


#3 Download reaspberry pi desktop image
https://www.raspberrypi.org/downloads/raspberry-pi-desktop/

#4 Create a VM for debian 64
- Start create VM wizard
- Select "Custom" option
- Under "Virtual Machine Hardware Compatibility" section, select Worksatation XX.x (most latest version beign appear)
- Under "Install operating system from" section, select "I will install operating system later"
- Select "Linux" as GUSET OPERATING SYSTEM and "Debian 10.x 64" as VERSION
- On next screen leave as default
- Assign "Total Processor core: 2" with any combination
- Assign at least 2GB of ram (Should be less than half of your physical machine's ram)
- Select "NAT" under networking section
- Leave I/O controller on DEFAULT
- Leave Virtual Disk type on DEFAULT
- Under "Disk" section, select "Create a newvirtual Disk"
- Allocate new disk size and provisioning types
	- 20 GB is sufficient
